description:
&lt;p&gt;We have a vacancy for 1 Clinical Teaching Fellow within the Department of Neurology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is fixed term until 3rd August 2021 and offers an exciting opportunity for experience in undergraduate medical education, delivering and developing clinical neurosciences teaching within the University Hospital of Wales. The post holders will work closely with lead tutors at three centres in Wales delivering the undergraduate neuroscience clinical module. The successful applicants will be expected to develop the core curriculum, to expand delivery of small group teaching and to enhance the system for student feedback and support. There is ample opportunity to put your own ‘stamp’ on the curriculum. Financial support is also provided for a Postgraduate Certificate or Diploma in Medical Education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is also an opportunity for the successful applicant to work in service delivery within the neurosciences in an area that is mutually beneficial to the applicant and department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is ideal for applicants considering applying for training numbers within neurosciences (neurology, neurosurgery, neurophysiology, neuropathology, neuroradiology), or for existing trainees taking a year out of programme to burnish their teaching credentials.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be responsible to Professor Neil Robertson and Dr Clinton Mitchell, lead tutors for undergraduate neurology teaching.&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for individuals who share our values in that:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;•We care about the people we serve and the people we work with&lt;br /&gt;•We trust one another&lt;br /&gt;•We respect one another&lt;br /&gt;•We take personable responsibility&lt;br /&gt;•We treat people with kindness&lt;br /&gt;•We act with integrity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
